**Wild Wonder 💡**

Did you know that there is a type of jellyfish that is **immortal**?! 🐳 The Turritopsis dohrnii, also known as the "immortal jellyfish," can transform its body into a younger state through a process called transdifferentiation. This means it can essentially revert back to its polyp stage and grow back into an adult again! Mind blown, right? 😲
